The attack comes after four men robbed a Clicks store at Vangate Mall in Athlone over the weekend. CAPE TOWN Police are hunting armed robbers who hit a KFC along Voortrekker Road in Parow.It s one of several business robberies in Cape Town recently.The police s Andre Traut says armed robbers stormed the KFC in Parow on Monday night. At approximately 10:15pm unknown unarmed suspect fled with an undisclosed amount of cash after holding staff at gunpoint. The attack comes after four men robbed a Clicks store at Vangate Mall in Athlone over the weekend.The MTN at Vangate Mall was also targeted in October. Last week, armed robbers stormed a Spur in Goodwood.(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)